@dimejune13 The error you describe does seem like there is some sort of BLOCK replication issue in HDFS, for example a file/block becomes under replicated if 1 or more nodes go down depending on your replication factor; it doesn't look like a version issue since it's intermittently working for you. If you see this issue again, could you please run the following command : 

http://hadoop.apache.org/docs/r2.7.1/hadoop-project-dist/hadoop-hdfs/HDFSCommands.html#fsck

Actually, if you can run this command every time on the partition_metadata file after the job to ensure it isn't a HDFS issue, that would give us more information to debug this. Since by the time you see the exception, the block may already have been fixed so we need to run it right after the job ends.

@pshivkumar may be we can do a hangout sometime? and try to understand whats going on? Might be a much easier route to understand..  
>> Is it possible to make this work with hive table schema without having to create avro schema file?
Hmmm. we need a schema to register the Hive table and that's derived from the parquet files.. What parquet version are you at?

@rchamarthi : Yes, I ran into the error as well and have the fix. It would be great if you could pull the PR and rebuild completely and test the demo.

Thanks 
Balaji.V
